{"questionId":"12506","questionHtml":"<p>Place the numbers&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2\\pi {\\text{,}}\\,\\, - 5{\\text{,}}\\,\\,{3^{ - 1}}\">\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{2^{\\frac{3}{2}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;in the correct position on the Venn diagram.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/2b286c1ad06d4f6252d7fff820f56c02f190d315.png\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p><img src=\"__IMG__/49e38212f5a59c64c198cc824cca951e7403ce34.png\"> &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)(A1)(A1)(A1)</em><em>&nbsp; &nbsp;</em></strong><strong><em>(C4)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> for each number in the correct position.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12506","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ1.T_7a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Place the numbers 2 π , − 5 , 3 − 1 and 2 3 2 in the correct position on the Venn diagram.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics a